69class Pipeline : public AllStatic {
70 public:
71 // Returns a new compilation job for the given JavaScript function.
72 static V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE std::unique_ptr<TurbofanCompilationJob>
73 NewCompilationJob(Isolate* isolate, Handle<JSFunction> function,
74 CodeKind code_kind, bool has_script,
75 BytecodeOffset osr_offset = BytecodeOffset::None());
76
77#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
78 // Run the pipeline for the WebAssembly compilation info.
79 // Note: We pass a pointer to {detected} as it might get mutated while
80 // inlining.
81 static void GenerateCodeForWasmFunction(
82 OptimizedCompilationInfo* info, wasm::CompilationEnv* env,
83 WasmCompilationData& compilation_data, MachineGraph* mcgraph,
84 CallDescriptor* call_descriptor,
85 ZoneVector<WasmInliningPosition>* inlining_positions,
86 wasm::WasmFeatures* detected);
87
88 // Run the pipeline on a machine graph and generate code.
89 static wasm::WasmCompilationResult GenerateCodeForWasmNativeStub(
90 CallDescriptor* call_descriptor, MachineGraph* mcgraph, CodeKind kind,
91 const char* debug_name, const AssemblerOptions& assembler_options,
92 SourcePositionTable* source_positions = nullptr);
93
94 static wasm::WasmCompilationResult
95 GenerateCodeForWasmNativeStubFromTurboshaft(
96 const wasm::WasmModule* module, const wasm::FunctionSig* sig,
97 wasm::WrapperCompilationInfo wrapper_info, const char* debug_name,
98 const AssemblerOptions& assembler_options,
99 SourcePositionTable* source_positions);
100
101 static bool GenerateWasmCodeFromTurboshaftGraph(
102 OptimizedCompilationInfo* info, wasm::CompilationEnv* env,
103 WasmCompilationData& compilation_data, MachineGraph* mcgraph,
104 wasm::WasmFeatures* detected, CallDescriptor* call_descriptor);
105
106 // Returns a new compilation job for a wasm heap stub.
107 static std::unique_ptr<TurbofanCompilationJob> NewWasmHeapStubCompilationJob(
108 Isolate* isolate, CallDescriptor* call_descriptor,
109 std::unique_ptr<Zone> zone, Graph* graph, CodeKind kind,
110 std::unique_ptr<char[]> debug_name, const AssemblerOptions& options);
111
112 static std::unique_ptr<compiler::turboshaft::TurboshaftCompilationJob>
113 NewWasmTurboshaftWrapperCompilationJob(
114 Isolate* isolate, const wasm::FunctionSig* sig,
115 wasm::WrapperCompilationInfo wrapper_info, const wasm::WasmModule* module,
116 std::unique_ptr<char[]> debug_name, const AssemblerOptions& options);
117#endif
118
119 // Run the pipeline on a machine graph and generate code.
120 static MaybeHandle<Code> GenerateCodeForCodeStub(
121 Isolate* isolate, CallDescriptor* call_descriptor, Graph* graph,
122 JSGraph* jsgraph, SourcePositionTable* source_positions, CodeKind kind,
123 const char* debug_name, Builtin builtin, const AssemblerOptions& options,
124 const ProfileDataFromFile* profile_data);
125
126 // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
127 // The following methods are for testing purposes only. Avoid production use.
128 // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
129
130 // Run the pipeline on JavaScript bytecode and generate code.
131 V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE static MaybeHandle<Code> GenerateCodeForTesting(
132 OptimizedCompilationInfo* info, Isolate* isolate);
133
134 // Run the pipeline on a machine graph and generate code. If {schedule} is
135 // {nullptr}, then compute a new schedule for code generation.
136 V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE static MaybeHandle<Code> GenerateCodeForTesting(
137 OptimizedCompilationInfo* info, Isolate* isolate,
138 CallDescriptor* call_descriptor, Graph* graph,
139 const AssemblerOptions& options, Schedule* schedule = nullptr);
140
141 // Run the instruction selector on a turboshaft graph and generate code.
142 V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE static MaybeHandle<Code> GenerateTurboshaftCodeForTesting(
143 OptimizedCompilationInfo* info, Isolate* isolate,
144 CallDescriptor* call_descriptor, PipelineData* data,
145 const AssemblerOptions& options);
146
147 // Run just the register allocator phases.
148 V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE static void AllocateRegistersForTesting(
149 const RegisterConfiguration* config, InstructionSequence* sequence,
150 bool run_verifier);
151
152 private:
153 DISALLOW_IMPLICIT_CONSTRUCTORS(Pipeline);
154};
